Both deliverables are written and the JSON validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**`transcript.json`** — 10 iterations, 22 hypotheses, 22 analyses. Key signed findings:
- feature_080 (continuous, 30–90, mean 65, plausibly age): r=+0.70, β=+0.176/unit
- feature_063 (3-level ordinal): level-2 vs level-0 = –2.35 mo
- Protective binaries: feature_042 (+1.10), feature_111 (+0.53); feature_019 (+0.476/unit)
- Harmful: feature_056 (–1.55), feature_048 (–0.98), feature_015 (–0.58), feature_040 (–0.47), feature_067 (–0.077/unit), feature_101 (–0.019/unit)
- Multivariable model R² = 0.79; feature_039 and feature_034 lose significance under adjustment (confounding)
- Race (feature_011, p=0.49) and insurance (feature_089, p=0.82): no main effect, no interaction with feature_042
- Five other 5-level ordinals (021/024/127/001/073): all null
- Real interactions: feature_056 × feature_080 (β=–0.011, p=3e-12); feature_080 × feature_019 (β=+0.005, p=0.0015); feature_042 × feature_080 (β=–0.003, p=0.044, weak)

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative walking through each iteration's hypotheses, signed effect, p-value, and supported/refuted verdict, with overall conclusions emphasizing the additive main-effect structure, absence of demographic disparities, and the few real interactions.
